post_text:
Hello LAE Families,

Given the current state of the COVID-19 health crisis, the local order by the Dallas County Health Department and guidance from the state and TEA, LAE will begin the 2020-2021 school year in remote only online instruction.

We expect to continue remote only instruction through the 1st six weeks. We will monitor the situation and adjust our plans in light of new information from state and local authorities as we move through the school year.

More information with details about learning at LAE this fall will be coming soon. Thank you for your continued trust.

Hello LAE Families,

We expect to continue remote only instruction through the 1st six weeks. We will monitor the situation and adjust our plans in light of new information from state and local authorities as we move through the school year.

More information with details about learning at LAE this fall will be coming soon. Thank you for your continued trust.

We hope that everyone is staying home or wearing a mask when you must go out. The Governor's new order requires mask be worn at this time in our community.

School administrators are monitoring the current COVID-19 situation and working with state and local authorities as we plan for 2020-2021. Information will be provided to families as soon as decisions are made. In the meantime, enjoy the remainder of our summer break and stay safe out there!

post_text:
Dear Parents,

Magic Tree House News!!
https://www.magictreehouse.com/go/

Random House Publishers and Mary Hope Osborne have created a wonderful online experience for students. You can listen to Ms. Osborne read from her books. There are all sorts of activities to do. The Magic Tree House books are big favorites, so let you students sign up and go on a journey to see dinosaurs or outer space or learn to be a knight!

This information will also be on the Library Google Classroom site. All K-4 Students have received an invite to come by everyday and read a poem and a joke, listen to story time and book talks.

Thank you,
Mrs. Wayne
School Librarian

post_text:
Hello LAE Families,

Planning is underway for distance learning. Our teachers have been very busy!

In addition, our technology team is working to help get computers ready to distribute to families in need. We will be reaching out to those families by the end of the week.

In the meanwhile, families who do not have internet access in their homes, should reach out to service providers who are offering free access in response to the COVID-19 crisis.

The following internet providers claim to offer free service for 60 days:

Spectrum---844-488-8395
Comcast--855-846-8376 (English); 855-765-6995 (Spanish)
Suddenlink (Altice)--888-633-0030

You may also check with your cellular phone provider to see if they have other low cost options for internet access in your home.

Please make getting internet in your home a priority over the next few days.

Thank you and Stay Safe!

post_text: Six of our former students graduated from Townview High School (ESSM & Health Professions) tonight! And many more have or are graduating this year! We couldn't find everyone in the sea of graduates, but check out who we did find! If you're a former student of LAE, we're looking for you! Let us know where you are and what you're up to now. Email our resident historian, Richard Tuck at richard.tuck@laetx.org. We'd love to see your graduation pictures too!
